This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the robustness of learning models to adversarial perturbations. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as adversarial training is a popular technique in the field of AI. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Gaussian features, which suggests it could also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper's focus on the tradeoff between standard and robust accuracy suggests it could also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
